TITLE: Running Terminal Commands for Creating Expo and React Native Projects
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates three different ways to create a new Expo or React Native project, including using create-expo-app with prebuild, create-expo-app with a bare minimum template, and react-native init with install-expo-modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/workflow/overview.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
$ npx create-expo-app MyApp && cd MyApp && npx expo prebuild

$ npx create-expo-app --template bare-minimum

$ npx react-native init MyApp && cd MyApp && npx install-expo-modules
```

