DESCRIPTION: This is a functional React Native component that uses expo-location to request location permissions and fetch the user's current position asynchronously. Dependencies include expo-location and react-native, and optionally expo-device for emulator checks. useEffect is used to initiate the permission request and location call on mount. Handles both Android/iOS permission flows and displays location or error in the UI. Inputs: none directly; outputs: displayed location as JSON string or error message. Limitations: Requires physical device for Android in Snack, and user must grant location permissions.
