TITLE: Creating Custom Keyboard Animation Hook in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a custom hook 'useGradualAnimation' that uses the 'useKeyboardHandler' hook from react-native-keyboard-controller. It tracks the keyboard height during animation frames, returning a shared value for use in animations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/keyboard-handling.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useKeyboardHandler } from 'react-native-keyboard-controller';
import Animated, { useAnimatedStyle, useSharedValue } from 'react-native-reanimated';

const useGradualAnimation = () => {
  const height = useSharedValue(0);

  useKeyboardHandler(
    {
      onMove: event => {
        'worklet';
        height.value = Math.max(event.height, 0);
      },
    },
    []
  );
  return { height };
};
```

