TITLE: Using CSS Modules in a React Component (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: This JSX snippet demonstrates how to import and use styles from a CSS Module file (`App.module.css`). It shows applying styles using the special `style` prop syntax (`{ $$css: true, _: styles.text }`) for React Native for Web components, using the `unstable_styles` import for `react-native-web`-safe styles, and using the standard `className` prop for web-only HTML elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v49.0.0/config/metro.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
```jsx App.js
import styles, { unstable_styles } from './App.module.css';

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <>
      <Text
        style={{
          // This is how react-native-web class names are applied
          $$css: true,
          _: styles.text,
        }}>
        Hello World
      </Text>
      <Text style={unstable_styles.text}>Hello World</Text>
      {/* Web-only usage: */}
      <p className={styles.text}>Hello World</p>
    </>
  );
}
```
```

