TITLE: Configuring GitHub Actions for EAS builds
DESCRIPTION: YAML configuration for GitHub Actions to set up a Node.js environment, install Expo CLI, and trigger EAS builds. It runs on push to main branch or manual trigger, and uses Expo's GitHub Action.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/build/building-on-ci.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
name: EAS Build
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
jobs:
  build:
    name: Install and build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 18.x
          cache: npm
      - name: Setup Expo and EAS
        uses: expo/expo-github-action@v8
        with:
          eas-version: latest
          token: ${{ secrets.EXPO_TOKEN }}
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci
      - name: Build on EAS
        run: eas build --platform all --non-interactive --no-wait
```

