TITLE: Defining View Event Callback and Module in Expo with Swift
DESCRIPTION: This Swift snippet defines an Expo Module (`CameraViewModule`) that registers a view (`CameraView`) capable of emitting an `onCameraReady` event using the `EventDispatcher`. The view's method `callOnCameraReady` triggers this event, sending a message payload to the React Native side. Dependencies include the Expo modules core for Swift. Key parameters: event name string and a dictionary payload. The pattern is intended for iOS in Expo modules, and limitations include platform specificity and type-checked payload structures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/modules/module-api.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
class CameraViewModule: Module {
  public func definition() -> ModuleDefinition {
    View(CameraView.self) {
      Events(
        "onCameraReady"
      )

      // ...
    }
  }
}

class CameraView: ExpoView {
  let onCameraReady = EventDispatcher()

  func callOnCameraReady() {
    onCameraReady([
      "message": "Camera was mounted"
    ]);
  }
}
```

