TITLE: Server Endpoint for Blurhash Generation
DESCRIPTION: Express.js endpoint implementation that accepts an image file and returns its blurhash representation
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/unversioned/sdk/image.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
app.post('/blurhash', upload.single('image'), async (req, res) => {
  const { file } = req;
  if (file === null) {
    res.status(400).json({ message: 'Image is missing' });
    return;
  }

  const componentX = req.body.componentX ?? 4;
  const componentY = req.body.componentY ?? 3;

  const { data, info } = await sharp(file.buffer).ensureAlpha().raw().toBuffer({
    resolveWithObject: true,
  });

  const blurhash = encode(data, info.width, info.height, componentX, componentY);
  res.json({ blurhash });
});
```

