TITLE: Inlining Environment Variables in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code adds support for inlining environment variables using the EXPO_PUBLIC_ prefix in Expo projects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/packages/@expo/cli/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const publicEnvs = Object.entries(process.env)
  .filter(([key]) => key.startsWith('EXPO_PUBLIC_'))
  .reduce((acc, [key, value]) => ({ ...acc, [key]: value }), {});

process.env.APP_MANIFEST = JSON.stringify({
  ...JSON.parse(process.env.APP_MANIFEST),
  extra: {
    ...JSON.parse(process.env.APP_MANIFEST).extra,
    ...publicEnvs,
  },
});
```

