TITLE: Adding Legacy Import Compatibility with Deprecation Warning
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to maintain backward compatibility with the old import syntax while adding a deprecation warning.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/guides/Migrating Universal Modules to TypeScript.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import * as FileSystem from './FileSystem';
export * from './FileSystem';

let wasImportWarningShown = false;
// @ts-ignore: Temporarily define an export named "FileSystem" for legacy compatibility
Object.defineProperty(exports, 'FileSystem', {
  get() {
    if (!wasImportWarningShown) {
      console.warn(
        `The syntax "import { FileSystem } from 'expo-file-system'" is deprecated. Use "import * as FileSystem from 'expo-file-system'" or import named exports instead. Support for the old syntax will be removed in SDK 34.`
      );
      wasImportWarningShown = true;
    }
    return FileSystem;
  },
});
```

