TITLE: Requesting Media Library Permissions in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the usePermissions hook to request media library permissions in a React component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/bluesky-social/expo/blob/main/packages/expo-media-library/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { usePermissions } from 'expo-media-library';

function MediaComponent() {
  const [status, requestPermission] = usePermissions();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (status !== 'granted') {
      requestPermission();
    }
  }, [status]);

  // Rest of the component
}
```

